<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Cylinder Head and Valves -
        Special Information - Tensioning Procedure for Torque-to-Yield Head Bolts
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Tensioning Procedure for Torque-to-Yield Head Bolts</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, do not use chlorinated solvents on bolts or crankcase tapped holes. Parts
                    should be clean, dry, and free of any chemical residuals other than engine oil.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position crankshaft at TDC for cylinder 1. Then rotate crankshaft 30 degrees past TDC.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 15W40 oil to clean bolts and washers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten each cylinder head bolt (long and short) to 136 N&#183;m (100 lbf&#183;ft) in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2100104101">cylinder head bolt tightening sequence</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten each cylinder head bolt (long and short) to 177 N&#183;m (130 lbf&#183;ft) in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2100104101">cylinder head bolt tightening sequence</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat Step 4 to obtain uniformity.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Add paint mark on each socket and bolt head and another mark 90 degrees clockwise on the
                cylinder head surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten each cylinder head bolt (long and short) by rotate each bolt 90 degrees (1/4 turn)
                in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f2100104101">cylinder head bolt tightening sequence</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2100104101" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/eg9199.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Cylinder head bolt tightening sequence</caption>
        </figure>
